# CEO Review (Plan) — TeleHealthy Voice Ops Console

## Assessment
Plan is genuinely build-ready for a winning 10/10 demo. Verified against brief + plan-eval.

- **Brief fit:** Client explicitly asked for a "simulated phone answering system and browser GPU based AI messaging system... demonstrated in a web app." Frontend-only Vite app with WebLLM (browser GPU) + scripted fallback maps the request precisely. No backend is the *right* call here, not a shortcut — there are no real telephony/CRM integrations to stand up, and simulation is what was requested.
- **Feature richness (10/10):** 4 functional tabs (Inbound, Outbound, Analytics, CRM) covering all 6 explicit reqs + all 3 nice-to-haves (healthcare copy, automation orchestration viz, EN/ES multilingual). Real working features: WebGPU AI conversation, intent detection, booking flow, SMS log, warm-transfer on low confidence, dynamic CRM-driven outbound scripts, charts + transcripts. This is full-featured, not a mockup.
- **Differentiator:** Browser-GPU LLM is the one thing that proves "shipped real voice AI before" better than any static deck — strong proposal leverage.

## Concurrence with eval's flagged forward deps (not plan failures)
1. WebLLM exact model ID + ESM CDN/npm import — researcher must confirm before `useWebLLM.js`. Most critical dependency.
2. Chart lib undecided (Chart.js CDN vs recharts) — demo-builder commits one; recharts preferred for Vite.
3. `InboundCall.jsx` carries 6 responsibilities at the 12-file cap — keep internally sectioned and lean.

## CEO additions for researcher/demo-builder (no re-run needed)
- WebLLM model download (hundreds of MB) is the #1 live-demo failure risk. Plan's mitigation is correct: lazy-load behind an explicit "Load AI" button, never auto-init on first paint, and make the scripted fallback indistinguishable in flow so the demo is fully exercisable with zero GPU/download. deploy-test will run headless (likely no WebGPU) — the scripted path MUST carry the full happy path so the live E2E passes.
- Keep a visible, honest "Simulated" / "Demo mode" label so the client reads it as a faithful prototype of their system, not a claim of live telephony.

No requirements missed; no earlier step needs re-running. Proceed to researcher.

## handoff
- produced: CEO sign-off on the plan; no redirect, no loop
- decisions: frontend-only + WebLLM/scripted-fallback approved as correct for the brief; 4-tab scope approved at 10/10
- next needs: researcher resolves WebLLM model ID + CDN import (critical), WebGPU support, GoHighLevel fields, Vapi/Retell call-UI conventions; demo-builder commits recharts and keeps InboundCall lean
- risks: WebLLM download size (lazy-load behind button + mandatory scripted fallback); deploy-test runs without WebGPU so scripted path must carry full happy flow

VERDICT: pass
